# agent-kanban — environment template. NO REAL VALUES in this file (it is committed).

# BOARD_BLOB_URL — the PUBLIC Vercel Blob URL of the board snapshot.
# loadBoard() fetches this SERVER-SIDE only; it is NEVER exposed to the browser.
# Leave it EMPTY for local dev (the app then reads data/board.json, falling back
# to data/board.sample.json). In the Vercel project env, set it to the URL printed
# by `npm run kanban:upload`.
BOARD_BLOB_URL=

# Courier credentials (#1050, #1405) — OIDC is the ONLY credential path (the
# long-lived RW token was revoked 2026-07-02 and its code paths removed).
#
# OIDC (short-lived, self-refreshing — no long-lived secret on disk):
#   vercel env pull .env.vercel-oidc.local --yes
# …run once from the linked repo root. The courier reads VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN +
# BLOB_STORE_ID from that file (gitignored via the .env.* rule) and re-pulls it
# automatically when the token is near expiry. Overrides:
#   OIDC_TOKEN_FILE       — token-file path (default: .env.vercel-oidc.local)
#   OIDC_REFRESH_SKEW_S   — refresh-ahead window in seconds (default: 900)
#
# With no reachable credential the hook logs a `skipped-no-token` record to
# data/sync.log (override the path via SYNC_LOG) and still exits 0 — never a
# silent no-op (#1158). Three consecutive non-success sync records fire an
# out-of-band notification.
